ent and system property guidance. If I include guidance, should I label it as advisory? I want to make sure I’m clear without restating deterministic actions unnecessarily.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\"action\":\"no_action\",\"summary\":\"No extra setup is needed: the resolved driver and its transitive runtime dependencies are sufficient, and the current failing coverage exercises Neo4j driver value/object-mapping APIs without requiring a Neo4j server, optional dependencies, or system properties.\",\"deterministic_setup\":[],\"agent_guidance\":\"\",\"risks\":[\"The library’s normal end-to-end usage connects to a Neo4j database over Bolt, and upstream integration tests use Docker/Testkit, but that is not required to reach meaningful coverage for this java-run failure or the existing generated-style tests.\",\"Optional modules such as Micrometer, SLF4J, and BlockHound are present as optional/static dependencies; only add them if generated tests explicitly target those integrations.\"]}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_017dbb32e6421348016a41dd81cde0819493c33b759d6e67e1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 350, "output": 675, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33793, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782701432189, "responseId": "resp_017dbb32e6421348016a41dd789ffc8194a398efc0e07367d4"}, "toolResults": []}
